\ Quantity-aware statistics: the matrix reductions and statistics accept a
\ dimensioned matrix, compute over the magnitude, and keep the unit — var in
\ the unit squared, index/count words and correlations bare. magnitude
\ ( v -- v' ) strips a quantity; any other value passes through.

[ 10 20 30 40 ] vector m to lengths

\ === reductions keep the unit ===
lengths sum . lengths mean . lengths max . lengths min . cr    \ 100 m 25 m 40 m 10 m
lengths var . lengths std . lengths se . cr                    \ 166.667 m^2 12.9099 m 6.45497 m
lengths median . lengths iqr . cr                              \ 25 m 15 m
lengths 0.95 ci . . cr                                         \ 39.25 m 10.75 m (high printed first)
lengths norm . cr                                              \ 54.7723 m
lengths cumulative-sum magnitude flatten . cr                  \ [ 10 30 60 100 ] as 1x4 grid
lengths 2 2 reshape . cr                                       \ 2x2 grid, unit m

\ === index and count words answer bare ===
lengths argsort transpose . cr                                 \ 0 1 2 3 as 1x4 grid
lengths argmax . lengths argmin . lengths size . cr            \ 3 0 4
lengths dim swap . . cr                                        \ 4 1

\ === magnitude: strip a quantity, pass anything else through ===
lengths magnitude sum . cr                                     \ 100 (bare)
5 m magnitude . 5 magnitude . "x" magnitude . cr               \ 5 5 x

\ === correlations are dimensionless whatever the operand units ===
[ 1 2 3 ] vector s [ 2 4 7 ] vector m correlation-pearson . cr     \ 0.993399
[ 1 2 3 4 ] vector s [ 2 4 7 9 ] vector m correlation-spearman . cr  \ 1
[ 1 2 3 4 ] vector s [ 2 4 7 9 ] vector m correlation-kendall . cr   \ 1
42 seed
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] vector s [ 2 4 7 9 11 ] vector m ' correlation-kendall 50 correlate-with :estimate @ . cr  \ 1

\ === dates: a column of instants is a dimensioned vector in s ===
"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z" iso>time 1 s / to epoch1
"2026-01-11T00:00:00Z" iso>time 1 s / to epoch2
[ epoch1 epoch2 ] vector s to dates
dates mean time>iso . cr                                       \ 2026-01-06T00:00:00Z
dates max dates min - 1 day / . cr                             \ 10

\ === missing values: the statistics skip NaN cells ===
[ 1 null 3 null ] vector to holes
holes sum . holes mean . holes max . holes min . cr            \ 4 2 3 1
holes nonmissing-count . holes norm . cr                       \ 2 3.16228
holes argmax . [ null 1 2 ] vector argmax . cr                 \ 2 1
[ 1 null 3 null 5 ] vector 0.5 quantile . cr                   \ 3
[ 1 null 3 null 5 ] vector var . cr                            \ 4
[ inf -inf ] vector sum none? . cr                             \ 1 (inf - inf is NaN, returned as null, not an error)

\ === correlations and regression drop incomplete pairs/rows ===
[ 1 2 null 4 ] vector [ 2 4 null 9 ] vector correlation-pearson . cr    \ 0.998625
[ 1 2 null 4 ] vector [ 2 4 null 9 ] vector correlation-kendall . cr    \ 1
[ 1 2 null 4 ] vector [ 2 4 null 9 ] vector correlation-spearman . cr   \ 1

\ === errors ===
[ 10 ] vector m var .                                          \ (needs at least 2 non-NaN elements)
[ null null ] vector max .                                     \ (all elements are NaN)
[ null null ] vector 0.5 quantile .                            \ (all elements are NaN)
[ 1 null ] vector [ 2 3 ] vector correlation-kendall .         \ (needs at least 2 complete pairs)
bye
